time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution iterates through the string s and checks if the substring from index i to (i + m - 1) is equal to part. If they are equal, it appends the substring to the result and increments i. This process continues until no more occurrences of part are found or the end of s is reached. The time complexity is O(n) because the algorithm iterates through the string once. The space complexity is O(1) because the algorithm uses a constant amount of space for the result string. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few comparisons and string operations, which are energy-efficient.

